enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: Shift LSB first. The first data bit of a data word is located at bit position 0.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: Shift MSB first. The first data bit of a data word is located at the bit position given by bit field SCTR.WLE.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: Receive and transmit data is shifted in and out one bit at a time through DX0 and DOUT0.

enumeratedValues.name: value3
enumeratedValues.description: Receive and transmit data is shifted in and out two bits at a time through two input stages (DX0 and DX3) and DOUT[1:0] respectively.

enumeratedValues.name: value4
enumeratedValues.description: Receive and transmit data is shifted in and out four bits at a time through four input stages (DX0, DX[5:3]) and DOUT[3:0] respectively.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The pin(s) with hardware pin control enabled are selected to be in input mode.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The pin(s) with hardware pin control enabled are selected to be in output mode.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The shift control signal is considered as inactive and data frame transfers are not possible.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The shift control signal is considered active if it is at 1-level. This is the setting to be programmed to allow data transfers.

enumeratedValues.name: value3
enumeratedValues.description: The shift control signal is considered active if it is at 0-level. It is recommended to avoid this setting and to use the inversion in the DX2 stage in case of a low-active signal.

enumeratedValues.name: value4
enumeratedValues.description: The shift control signal is considered active without referring to the actual signal level. Data frame transfer is possible after each edge of the signal.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The data word contains 1 data bit located at bit position 0.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The data word contains 2 data bits located at bit positions [1:0].

enumeratedValues.name: value3
enumeratedValues.description: The data word contains 15 data bits located at bit positions [14:0].

enumeratedValues.name: value4
enumeratedValues.description: The data word contains 16 data bits located at bit positions [15:0].

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of SCTR.WLE and TCSR.EOF is disabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of SCTR.WLE and TCSR.EOF is enabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of PCR.CTR[23:16] is disabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of PCR.CTR[23:16] is disabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of FLE is disabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of FLE is enabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of bit WA is disabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of bit WA is enabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of bits SCTR.DSM and SCTR.HPCDIR is disabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The automatic update of bits SCTR.DSM and SCTR.HPCDIR is enabled.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is not considered as first word of a frame.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is considered as first word of a frame. A currently running frame is finished and MSLS becomes deactivated (respecting the programmed delays).

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is not considered as last word of an SSC frame.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is considered as last word of an SSC frame.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is not valid for transmission.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is valid for transmission and a transmission start is possible. New data should not be written to a TBUFx input location while TDV = 1.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is not considered as invalid after it has been loaded into the transmit shift register. The loading of the TBUF data into the shift register does not clear TDV.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF is considered as invalid after it has been loaded into the shift register. In ASC and IIC mode, TDV is cleared with the TBI event, whereas in SSC and IIS mode, it is cleared with the RSI event. TDSSM = 1 has to be programmed if an optional data buffer is used.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: A transmission start of the data word in TBUF is disabled. If a transmission is started, the passive data level is sent out.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: A transmission of the data word in TBUF can be started if TDV = 1.

enumeratedValues.name: value3
enumeratedValues.description: A transmission of the data word in TBUF can be started if TDV = 1 while DX2S = 0.

enumeratedValues.name: value4
enumeratedValues.description: A transmission of the data word in TBUF can be started if TDV = 1 while DX2S = 1.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: Bit TCSR.TE is set if DX2T becomes active while TDV = 1.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF will be transmitted after a falling edge of WA has been detected (referring to PSR.WA).

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The data word in TBUF will be transmitted after a rising edge of WA has been detected (referring to PSR.WA).

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The latest data word transmission has not been started for the first word of a data frame.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The latest data word transmission has been started for the first word of a data frame.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The latest start of a data word transmission has taken place while no valid data was available. As a result, the transmission of a data words with passive level (SCTR.PDL) has been started.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The latest start of a data word transmission has taken place with valid data from TBUF.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: Since TVC has been set, at least one data buffer underflow condition has occurred.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: Since TVC has been set, no data buffer underflow condition has occurred.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The trigger event has not yet been detected. A transmission of the data word in TBUF can not be started.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The trigger event has been detected (or the trigger mechanism is switched off) and a transmission of the data word in TBUF can not be started.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: Only one sample is taken per bit time. The current input value is sampled.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: Three samples are taken per bit time and a majority decision is made.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The number of stop bits is 1.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The number of stop bits is 2.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The bus idle detection is switched off and bits PSR.TXIDLE and PSR.RXIDLE are set automatically to enable data transfers without checking the inputs before.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The bus is considered as idle after a number of consecutive passive bit times defined by SCTR.FLE plus 2 (in the case without parity bit) or plus 3 (in the case with parity bit).

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: If a collision is detected, the transmitter stops its data transmission, outputs a 1, sets bit PSR.COL and generates a protocol interrupt. In order to allow data transmission again, PSR.COL has to be cleared by software.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The pulse length is equal to the bit length (no shortened 0).

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The pulse length of a 0 bit is 2 time quanta.

enumeratedValues.name: value3
enumeratedValues.description: The pulse length of a 0 bit is 3 time quanta.

enumeratedValues.name: value4
enumeratedValues.description: The pulse length of a 0 bit is 8 time quanta.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: Flag PSR[9] is not modified depending on the receiver status.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: Flag PSR[9] is set during the complete reception of a frame.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: Flag PSR[9] is not modified depending on the transmitter status.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: Flag PSR[9] is set during the complete transmission of a frame.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The MCLK generation is disabled and the MCLK signal is 0.

enumeratedValues.description: The MSLS generation is disabled (MSLS = 0). This is the setting for SSC slave mode.

enumeratedValues.name: value2

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The SELO outputs have the same polarity as the MSLS signal (active high).

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The SELO outputs have the inverted polarity to the MSLS signal (active low).

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: The current data frame is considered as finished when the last bit of a data word has been sent out and the transmit buffer TBUF does not contain new data (TDV = 0).

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: The MSLS signal is kept active also while no new data is available and no other end of frame condition is reached. In this case, the software can accept delays in delivering the data without automatic deactivation of MSLS in multi-word data frames.

enumeratedValues.name: value1
enumeratedValues.description: Resetting bit INIT enables the participation of the node in the CAN traffic. If the CAN node is in the bus-off state, the ongoing bus-off recovery (which does not depend on the INIT bit) is continued. With the end of the bus-off recovery sequence the CAN node is allowed to take part in the CAN traffic. If the CAN node is not in the bus-off state, a sequence of 11 consecutive recessive bits must be detected before the node is allowed to take part in the CAN traffic.

enumeratedValues.name: value2
enumeratedValues.description: Setting this bit terminates the participation of this node in the CAN traffic. Any ongoing frame transfer is cancelled and the transmit line goes recessive. If the CAN node is in the bus-off state, then the running bus-off recovery sequence is continued. If the INIT bit is still set after the successful completion of the bus-off recovery sequence, i.e. after detecting 128 sequences of 11 consecutive recessive bits (11 1), then the CAN node leaves the bus-off state but remains inactive as long as INIT remains set.
